ABUJA (Sundiata Post) President Muhammadu Buhari has officially announced his intention to seek a second term in the 2019 presidential election. This was reported on Monday by the official twitter account of the Nigerian Presidency (@NGRPresident) ”President @MBuhari has just announced his intention to seek the presidential ticket of the All Progressives Congress (APC) and contest for a second term of Office in the 2019 elections,” reads the tweet.  The news was further corroborated by Kaduna State Governor, Mallam Nasir Elrufai on his official twitter account (@elrufai). ”BREAKING NEWS: PMB has just announced to APC NEC his intention to run for a second term of office. Alhamdulillah. – Nasir El-Rufai.” 